                <fr:addr type="user">//forester/jms-00CY</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-00CY.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Breaking changes">Breaking changes</fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p><fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-00CW.xml" title="Forester 3.0" addr="//forester/jms-00CW" type="local">Forester 3.0</fr:link> introduces a number of breaking changes to the source language in order to facilitate maintainability, diagnostic support, and extensibility of both the Forester tool and your individual <fr:link href="foreign-forester-tfmt-000R.xml" title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes" addr="//forester/tfmt-000R" type="local">forests</fr:link>.</fr:p>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//forester/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>11</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:anchor>8427</fr:anchor>
                    <fr:addr type="user">//forester/jms-00CZ</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-00CZ.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Fall-through of undefined identifiers">Fall-through of undefined identifiers</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Change</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <fr:p>The fall-through for undefined identifiers in XML mode is removed in <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-00CW.xml" title="Forester 3.0" addr="//forester/jms-00CW" type="local">Forester 3.0</fr:link>: previously when an identifier <fr:code><![CDATA[\foo]]></fr:code> was undefined, it was possible to write <fr:code><![CDATA[\foo[attr]{value}{body}]]></fr:code> and have this be rendered in XML to <fr:code><![CDATA[<foo attr="value">body</foo>]]></fr:code>.</fr:p>
                    <fr:p>This behavior has been removed, but you can nonetheless write <fr:code><![CDATA[\xml{foo}[attr]{value}{body}]]></fr:code> to achieve the same. For content that is being rendered by either LaTeX or KaTeX, simple fallthrough (naturally without attributes or arguments) is supported; therefore <fr:code><![CDATA[#{\alpha}]]></fr:code> will render to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//forester/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>11</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:anchor>8428</fr:anchor>
                    <fr:addr type="user">//forester/jms-00D0</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-00D0.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Primitive formatting commands">Primitive formatting commands</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Change</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <fr:p>As a consequence of the <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-00CZ.xml" title="Forester 3.0 › breaking changes › fall-through of undefined identifiers" addr="//forester/jms-00CZ" type="local">changed fallthrough behavior</fr:link>, several new primitives have been added to the source language, including <fr:code><![CDATA[\p]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\em]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\strong]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\ol]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\ul]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\li]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\blockquote]]></fr:code>, and <fr:code><![CDATA[\pre]]></fr:code>.</fr:p>
                    <fr:p>You can add further commands to your primitives using a combination of <fr:code><![CDATA[\def]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\iftex]]></fr:code>, and <fr:code><![CDATA[\xml]]></fr:code>.</fr:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
